channel.title: Loggin message ( not what you think)
channel.description: Well i used skillz as a base, and i heavily modified it. Now, i found the first loggin message, Welcome to ____ and i put my server name. But, any time you log in, after that, it says created by mythix. Iv searched everywere in all the java files, and it couldnt find it. Where else could it be called from?

item.title: Loggin message ( not what you think)
item.dc:creator: @the_predi the predi
item.description:
@the_predi wrote:

[quote=“gio2, post:4, topic:194860”][quote author=fvhfughdfuvfuhu link=topic=259206.msg2150048#msg2150048 date=1207002517]
why are you tring to leech?
[/quote]
Im trying to leech? I used the source as a base, and it is way diffrent then the source i used. People are going to think we leeched if we cant even bother to remove the log in message.

The server knows your not the owner, it knows…

As i said before. Its way diffrent then it was. Iv added
Castle Wars(was kinda there, i fixed it)
Pest Control
Farming Animations / Weed’s
Reduced the Client class size by 400kb reducing it to 600kb and removing junk from the process
Made training harder
Custom Client items added to it
Fixed Theiving
Fixed Highscores
Removed any trace of silab from it
Re-did the GS Minigame
Made Web HighScores
And made Bans, Npc’s and Shop’s load from a mysql database.
Added Jad Minigame
And more.

So your saying, i should not get credit for anything?[/quote]

wow u look a great coder !

hm just try client.java normally its always over there otherways its maybe into your client that u are using

I hope i helped u
